When reached for comment, Mrs Ochae downplayed her sacking.The changes were communicated by the Governor’s Press Director Mr Nicholas Anyuor. Migori Governor Okoth Obado has announced changes in his cabinet with effect from December 16, dropping a long term ally in a new formation. 
In Wednesday's reshuffle, county Environment CS Mrs Elizabeth Ochae lost her portfolio after the department was merged with that of Water, Energy, Environment and Disaster Management which will be headed by Mrs Rebecca Maroa.



