However, when reached for comment, Mrs Ochae downplayed her sacking.
“There is no cause for an alarm. Life goes on and I want to thank the governor for giving me a chance to serve in his government,” Mrs Ochae said.
This is the second time Mrs Ochae is being expunged from Governor Obado’s administration after she was ejected from the trade department before being reinstated to the cabinet in a different capacity.
The executive changes were communicated by the Governor’s Press Director Mr Nicholas Anyuor.



