Mrs Scholastica Obiero retained her position in the Finance and Economic Planning department as an executive with Mrs Roselyn Otieno appointed as the Chief Officer.
Other changes
Mr Moses Chamwada maintained his position as the transport executive with Mr Samuel Ochieng appointed as a chief officer in the same department.
In the health docket, Col Rt. Joseph Nyamita comes on board as the chief officer replacing Madam Iscah Oluoch who has been moved to the department of Public Service Management and Administration.
Mr Nyamita will be deputised by Mr Dalmas Oyugi and Ms Pauline Amollo as Chief officers in Medical Services and Public Health respectively.
Mrs Oluoch, on her part, will be deputised by Mr Edward Kabaka and Mr Charles Gucha as Chief Officers in the Public Service Management and Administration and ICT and e-government respectively.



